title: What is the Muslim Brotherhood – explained in 30 seconds
summary: The Muslim Brotherhood, one of the Arab world's oldest and most influential Islamist movements, continues to play a significant role in regional politics. Founded in Egypt in 1928, it has shaped political discourse and policies across various countries. Despite facing repression and challenges, the movement maintains a dedicated following and influences contemporary Islamist thought.

title: Brisbane storms and hail leave nearly 100,000 without power as trees downed and roofs stripped
summary: Severe weather in the city caused over 880,000 lightning strikes and hailstones up to 12cm in diameter. High winds were the primary factor leading to widespread power outages. The storm's intensity resulted in significant disruptions across the region.

title: ‘An idealized version of LA’: fabled mid-century Stahl house on sale for first time
summary: A historic home in the Hollywood Hills, originally built for $37,500 and renowned for a photo by photographer Julius Shulman, has been listed for $25 million. The property showcases a blend of architectural significance and modern luxury. Its steep price reflects the home's unique heritage and location.
